Almost 30 associations and organizations endorsed an open letter addressed to King Norodom Sihamoni.
Associations and Non-Governmental Organizations,the controversial bill was already approved by lawmakers of the National Assembly on 13 July 2015 and the Senate on 24 July 2015
The bill will need to be firstly approved by the Constitutional Council before final approval by the King.
The proposed bill has been widely criticized, as it is used as a political tool by the ruling government in order to restrict NGOs’ activities in Cambodia.